{{see|Ancien Régime}}

==French & English==
===Etymology===
French ''Ancient Régime'', ''Old Rule'', ''Old Order''; the word first appeared in English in print in 1794.

===Noun===
'''ancien régime''' (''plural:'' '''[[anciens régimes]]''')

# {{cattag|pejorative connotation}} A system of government long since supplanted by another; particularly a state of [[feudalism]] with an absolute [[monarchy]] supported by the doctrine of the [[Divine Right of Kings]] or [[天命]] with the explicit consent of an established [[church]].